						<summary>

						<p>Sculptured slab lying in front of the Pushpēśvara temple on the hill.</p>						

						<p>Circa 13th century.</p>						

						<p>This record seems to register the death of a hero. It refers to Siddavaṭṭa as the southern door-entrance to Śriparvata. All the other details are lost.</p>						

						<p>2. The rest of the record is badly damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
